dataset_description.json.Name: NIMH-CompyPsych MMI
dataset_description.json.Acknowledgements: Preparation of this dataset for sharing used the computational resources of the NIH HPC (high-performance computing) Biowulf cluster (http://hpc.nih.gov).
Funding: National Institute of Mental Health Grant ZIA-MH002957-01 to AS
ReferencesAndLinks: Keren H., Zheng C., Jangraw D.C., Chang K., Vitale A., Rutledge R.B., Pereira F., Nielson D.M., Stringaris A. (2021). The temporal representation of experience in subjective mood. eLife, 2021;10:e62051, DOI: 10.7554/eLife.62051
EthicsApprovals: All participants in this study were enrolled in the Characterization and Treatment of Adolescent Depression study approved by the NIH IRB under protocol number 18-M-0037.

handedness.Description: handedness of the participant as reported by the participant

group.Description: experimental group the participant belonged to

Levels.MDD: Participants with current, ongoing, or historical depression

MFQ.LongName: Mood and Feelings Questionnaire total score
MFQ.Description: Total score from self report on the short version of the Mood and Feelings Questionnaire (MFQ) (Angold et al., 1995), which measures depressive symptoms in children and adolescents.

SHAPS.Description: Total score from self report on the SHAPS (Snaith et al., 1995), which measures anhedonia symptoms.

README: For details on subjects, tasks, or analyses, please see the accompanying manuscript: https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.62051. For any questions, please contact Dylan.Nielson@gmail.com, ORCID: 0000-0003-4613-6643.

onset.Description: Time the draw command on the monitor starts in seconds in reference to the scan start time of the block. Negative times indicate onsets before the first scanning block.

onset_delay.Description: Difference between onset time and intended display time

onset_unadjusted.Description: True onset time in seconds without subtracting scanner start time

trial_number.Description: Sequential numbering of gambling trials accross all runs.

block.Description: Block of task data, blocks correspond to functional runs.

duration.Description: Time in seconds that this phase of the trial is presented

mood_target.Description: Targeted mood value of the block, higher value represents happier mood

outcome.Description: Outcome of the trial - result of the gamble or certain

question_duration.Description: Duration of question in mood rating trials

rating.Description: Whether or not the participant was asked to rate their mood

response.Description: Value of the key response. 2 is gamble, 4 is certain outcome.

rt.Description: Reaction time in seconds since onset time

rt_time.Description: Time of the response in seconds since the start of the scan

slider_response.Description: Value of slider response for mood ratings - higher value represents happier mood

trial_phase.Description: Which phase of the trial the event represents

trial_type.Description: Categorization of the trial on the basis of the cue type and the result
